{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"body":"STATUS 2026-07-12 (/rebar-implement): CLAIMED (in_progress), plan HARDENED + signed through the claim gate, NOT yet implemented. New G7 leaf-parent-containment plan-review criterion. KEY design (settled during claim remediation): G7 is exec:AGENT and reads the parent ticket at RUNTIME via its always-available show_ticket tool (parent_id is already in the ticket-graph context via pass1._ticket_graph_blob) — NO new context-plumbing. Register G7 in CANONICAL_LLM + AGENT_TIER but NOT CODEBASE_GROUNDED (tooling is granted by agentic execution_mode per registry.py:62-65, not by CODEBASE_GROUNDED; G7 grounds against the ticket store, not code). Add a require_parent_id applies_at axis, validated in criteria/overlay.py::_validate_routing_entry (190-212) AND registry.validate_packaged_routing, threaded via orchestrator.route_criteria. New reviewers/plan_review_G7.md rubric (parent-wins; instructs show_ticket(parent_id)) + one parent-realign coach move in passes.py MOVE_REGISTRY + add G7 to workflow/gates/plan-review.yaml criteria list + regenerate docs/plan-review-criteria-guide.md. Ships advisory 0.95; promotion-path doc committed at docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/g7-promotion-path.md (fire-rate jq query over plan_review_result_v1 sidecars + 0.6-0.7 band). REMAINING: implement under held-out TDD (routing fires leaf-with-parent only; fixture parent/leaf semantics contained/exceeding/contradicting; validate_packaged_routing()==[]), commit, push, close."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783907690274749001,"uuid":"dfc64264-b0b5-42fe-892a-0065bd47e445"}